reviewText:
One of the best rhythmic games out on the Steam store (this and Beyond the Echo, be sure to check that title out if you enjoyed this game), I truly enjoyed Frederic: Ressurection of Music, but found it quite short, with little replay value. Still worth buying on sale. Recommend it!

Pros:
- High quality voice acting;
- Really enjoyable songs!;
- Quite beautiful background art
- Very original levels, in a way that each setup for a level is very different from the one before;

Cons:
- Poorly designed character movement;
- Chopin and expert levels can really be tricky with a keyboard;
- Only 9 levels, that are very short, providing, all and all, about 3-4 hours of gameplay.

